rComments: Lets start by saying that he gets his test questions from past tests- that he posts on portal. So if you do them, understand them and write them on your cheat sheet you get an easy A . Lots of people skipped lectures because of this, but he is funny and gives hints in class. This also saves you from cramming
Very good professor. Cheatsheet is very useful. It seems like he would not be teaching next year tho.

I took ECO220Y5F, which condenses the course in one term. If you're taking this as well, do not get discouraged after the first test, the second and third test will only get better. Probability theory is the only difficult segment of this course, the other two remaining segments are easy. TIP: Write a lot of examples on your permitted cheat sheet.

Great prof. Class is fairly easy anyway with the help of cheat sheets and past tests, but he has clear,  occasionally humourous lectures, and is respected and respectful! Really enjoyed being in his class!
meh

rComments: Don't get caught on your phone in class, other than that, have a good cheat sheet with past test answers and you'll get an easy B
30% of the students attended Anderson's lectures and the class average is a B+ in the end. Pretty much sums up how easy his statistics course is. Test questions are straight forward.

Professor Anderson is so far my favourite economics professor. His lectures were interesting as he cracked jokes and you could tell that he cared about his students. He definitely knows his material and I would definitely recommend every economics or commerce student at UTM take one of his classes in the future.
He is a good proff, however he doesnt know how to properly prepare us for his midterms. just do all tut questions and you have to look at past tests.

Best prof I've ever had. Go to all the lectures and use the lecture notes he posts on blackboard they are very useful. he's extremely helpful if you go to his office hours with specific problems or topics you need help with and he will explain until you get it. not an easy course but with a little work you can do well
Not that great at explaining. Tests are just to see if you can copy off a cheat sheet. If you want to learn, don't take this class.

The course is more like a gamble: put the right stuff on cheat sheet, you're set; if not, you're screwed. His lectures have too much theory and not enough applications. Problems are in tutorials but TAs are so useless. He needs to be more strict with the TAs.

Great prof. Very helpful and supportive. He'll give you the help you need. He's incredibly smart. His teaching style is simple and straight forward, no complications. I took his course in the summer so I had 2 hours every day 4 days a week. But it wasn't that bad, he made much easier and more fun. He's definitely the best prof I've ever had.

Hands down, one of the best Profs I've ever had. Also, I got my highest mark in university in his class. I know very few read his notes but they are helpful. The keys to this class are to get the good TA, must make own cheat sheet (don't be tempted to buy cheat sheet from someone else), and don't skip his lectures.
Great guy, very funny. He doesnt bump grades tho. I was stuck at 76 but didnt do any favours. Just do the past tests and have a perfect cheatsheet.

Great guy, and the best teacher I have ever had at any level. He just shows up with no notes, cracks a bunch of jokes grabs some chalk and starts teaching. I had stats 6-8 pm on a Monday and enjoyed his class immensely.
Great guy! Studied other books before class which made formulas more comprehensible. Do past exams. Wish I spent more time talking to him!
I liked him! For some reason he reminds me of santa claus because he's a real jolly guy and he made the class fun.
Very cute and very funny!!! Makes stats a bit more interesting! Gotta practice past tests and you should do good in the course!!! Wears different cool bow ties!!
the most wonderful pro I've ever met

Do past test questions & the assignments and put those on your cheat sheet;then ur good to go! What a high spirited prof with a barrel full of laughs and stories that never cease to surprise! He makes Eco Stats a lot more interesting than I could have ever imagined. Wonderful prof.
